metadata.title: Cessna 310
aws::graph::propositions: On July 19, 1967, a Boeing 727 operating as Piedmont Airlines Flight 22 collided with a Cessna 310 near Hendersonville, North Carolina.
The collision between Piedmont Airlines Flight 22 and the Cessna 310 killed all 79 people on board the Boeing 727.
The collision between Piedmont Airlines Flight 22 and the Cessna 310 killed all 3 people in the Cessna 310.
On October 16, 1972, US Congressman Nick Begich of Alaska disappeared over Alaska while flying in a Cessna 310C.
On October 16, 1972, US Congressman Hale Boggs of Louisiana disappeared over Alaska while flying in a Cessna 310C.
The Cessna 310C carrying Nick Begich and Hale Boggs was being used during a campaign trip.
On October 4, 1975, a chartered Cessna 310Q crashed on final approach to New Hanover County Airport.
The Cessna 310Q was transporting wrestlers Bob Bruggers, Ric Flair, Johnny Valentine, and Tim Woods to a professional wrestling match in Wilmington, North Carolina.
The Cessna 310Q was also transporting promoter David Crockett to a professional wrestling match in Wilmington, North Carolina.
Bob Bruggers was seriously injured in the Cessna 310Q crash.
Ric Flair was seriously injured in the Cessna 310Q crash.
Johnny Valentine was paralyzed in the Cessna 310Q crash.
The pilot of the Cessna 310Q subsequently died of injuries sustained in the crash.

text:
On July 19, 1967, a Boeing 727 operating as Piedmont Airlines Flight 22 collided with a Cessna 310 near Hendersonville, North Carolina, killing all 79 people on board the Boeing 727 and the three people in the Cessna.
On October 16, 1972, US Congressmen Nick Begich of Alaska, and Hale Boggs of Louisiana, disappeared over Alaska while flying in a 310C during a campaign trip.
On October 4, 1975, a chartered 310Q crashed on final approach to New Hanover County Airport while transporting wrestlers Bob Bruggers, Ric Flair, Johnny Valentine and Tim Woods and promoter David Crockett  to a professional wrestling match in nearby Wilmington, North Carolina. Bruggers and Flair were seriously injured, while Valentine was paralyzed and the pilot subsequently died of his injuries.
